        {
          "id": "f25bcpjBuFEuyMFO",
          "content": {
            "type": "Text",
            "format": "html",
            "text": [
              "<p>She says you just have to find the point you need on the graph.</p>"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "TILEvnsTjtBwZJAE",
          "display": "teacher",
          "content": {
            "type": "Text",
            "format": "html",
            "text": [
              "<p><em>Emily’s Strategy</em></p><p>The point on the graph tells you the total amount of food and the cups of protein. Then you can subtract those amounts to get the cups of fiber.</p><p>For example (15, 6):</p><p>The 15 is the total amount of food.</p><p>The 6 is the number of cups that are protein.  15 – 6 = 9 which would be the number of cups of fiber that are needed.</p>"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "lDpk7VmOZclFWcHE",
          "content": {
            "type": "Text",
            "format": "html",
            "text": [
              "<p><strong>Situation C. Population Growth</strong></p><p>Chimpanzees are an endangered species. They are extinct in several of their original countries. They are extensively studied in biomedical research to gain an understanding of various diseases that result in substantial sickness.</p><p>A research team was recording the growth of chimpanzees in two remote areas. In one year, the population in Area Amber grew from 15 to 19 chimpanzees. The population in Area Blue grew from 11 to 16 chimpanzees. Which area has the greatest growth in one year? Explain why.</p>"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "TILEGrumG79Zzvsa",
          "display": "teacher",
          "content": {
            "type": "Text",
            "format": "html",
            "text": [
              "<p>Area Amber grew from 15 to 19</p><p>The increase is 4 chimpanzees for every 15.</p><p>About 26% increase.</p>"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "1LN6fpAfgm_6Kj-p",
          "title": "Area Amber Proportion",
          "display": "teacher",
          "content": {
            "type": "Expression",
            "latexStr": "\\frac{4}{15}=\\frac{0.26666...}{1}=\\frac{26.6666...}{100}"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "TILEFKthDQH8AJdS",
          "display": "teacher",
          "content": {
            "type": "Text",
            "format": "html",
            "text": [
              "<p>Area Blue grew from 11 to 16 chimpanzees</p><p>The increase is 11chimpanzees for every 16.</p><p>68.75% increase</p><p>This is a greater growth.</p>"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "wYvGSZhFNDQxBotQ",
          "title": "Area Blue Proportion",
          "display": "teacher",
          "content": {
            "type": "Expression",
            "latexStr": "\\frac{11}{16}=\\frac{0.6875}{1}=\\frac{68.75}{100}"
          }
        }
