              "<p><strong>Scarlett</strong>:  We were disappointed that we didn’t have really nice proportional data to work with.</p><p><strong>Teacher</strong>: How did you know it wasn’t proportional?</p><p><strong>Carter</strong>: We looked at 5 seconds and 15 seconds. That would be multiplying by 3 and if you multiplied the water amounts by 3, it didn’t work?</p><p><strong>Kathy</strong>: I don’t know what you mean, Carter.</p><p>Carter draws this on their data:</p>"
