              "<p><strong>Today&#x27;s Activity: Identifying Stakeholders</strong></p><p>You just identified some of your<strong> stakeholders</strong>! </p><p>A <strong>stakeholder</strong> is any person who<em> cares about</em> your design solution or <em>will be affected by it </em>in some way. In this case, stakeholders are people in your community that you will affect if you create a design solution for water conservation. They <em>have a stake</em> in your design solution.</p><p>A design solution can affect many people:</p><ul><li>people that care about the design solution</li><li>people that use the design solution (even if they don&#x27;t care about it very much)</li><li>people that want the design solution in their community (even if they might not use it)</li><li>people that might not want the design solution in their community</li><li>people that will give money, time, or other resources to create the design solution</li></ul>"
